---
title: "RAG Pipeline — Remediated State Machine"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> PrepareConversation: Receive OpenAI-format messages

    PrepareConversation: Normalize conversation in backend
    note right of PrepareConversation
        Extract raw_query from request.messages.
        Build conversation_context using summary + recent turns.
        Rewrite follow-ups into resolved_query.
        Backend also classifies title / tags / follow_ups tasks.
    end note

    PrepareConversation --> TaskRoute
    state TaskRoute <<choice>>

    TaskRoute --> RunAuxiliaryTask: task_type != chat
    TaskRoute --> InputGuard: task_type == chat

    RunAuxiliaryTask: Run backend-owned auxiliary prompt
    note right of RunAuxiliaryTask
        Uses chat history from request.messages.
        Skips retrieval and citation flow.
    end note
    RunAuxiliaryTask --> TraceOutput

    InputGuard: Input Guard Check
    note right of InputGuard
        POST /classify
        text = resolved_query
        Guard service uses torch.inference_mode()
        and logs latency + GPU memory metrics.
    end note

    InputGuard --> ReturnApology: UNSAFE
    InputGuard --> EmbedQuery: SAFE

    EmbedQuery: Embed resolved_query
    note right of EmbedQuery
        Qwen3-Embedding-0.6B
        prompt_name="query"
        Logs before/after memory snapshots.
    end note

    EmbedQuery --> HybridRetrieve

    HybridRetrieve: Retrieve from Qdrant
    note right of HybridRetrieve
        Try sparse encoding with underthesea + BM25.
        On success: hybrid_search(dense, sparse).
        On sparse error: dense-only fallback.
    end note

    HybridRetrieve --> Rerank

    Rerank: Rerank candidates sequentially
    note right of Rerank
        Qwen3-Reranker-0.6B
        yes/no logit scoring
        Uses torch.inference_mode()
        and request-level GPU metrics logging.
    end note

    Rerank --> EvalFallback
    EvalFallback: Evaluate web fallback trigger

    state fallback_check <<choice>>
    EvalFallback --> fallback_check
    fallback_check --> WebFallback: too few chunks OR weak top score
    fallback_check --> CombineContext: retrieval confidence acceptable

    WebFallback: Tavily search(resolved_query)
    note right of WebFallback
        Web results carry source_type="web"
        and stable context_id metadata.
    end note
    WebFallback --> CombineContext

    CombineContext: Build final_context + citation_pool
    note right of CombineContext
        final_context is generation content.
        citation_pool is keyed by context_id and
        preserves provenance across hybrid + web.
    end note

    CombineContext --> CheckEmpty
    state empty_check <<choice>>
    CheckEmpty --> empty_check
    empty_check --> ReturnNoContext: no usable context
    empty_check --> GenerateAnswer: context available

    ReturnNoContext: Return no-context answer
    ReturnNoContext --> TraceOutput

    GenerateAnswer: Generate draft answer
    note right of GenerateAnswer
        Prompt includes conversation_context,
        source metadata, and raw_query.
        LLM is instructed to cite inline using
        [[cite:context_id]] placeholders.
    end note

    GenerateAnswer --> OutputGuard

    OutputGuard: Output Guard Check
    note right of OutputGuard
        prompt = resolved_query
        Retry once with safety feedback if needed.
    end note

    OutputGuard --> RetryGeneration: first pass unsafe
    OutputGuard --> BuildCitations: safe
    RetryGeneration --> RecheckOutput
    RecheckOutput: Re-run output guard
    RecheckOutput --> BuildCitations: safe
    RecheckOutput --> ReturnApology: still unsafe

    BuildCitations: Validate and render citations
    note right of BuildCitations
        Parse valid placeholder ids from answer.
        Repair once if answer has no valid citations.
        Fallback to deterministic top citations if repair fails.
        Render final inline markdown links [title](url)
        or title (source) when URL is missing.
    end note

    BuildCitations --> TraceOutput

    TraceOutput: Compact root trace output
    note right of TraceOutput
        LangSmith root output = answer, citations,
        task_type, resolved_query.
        Raw graph state and generation_prompt
        remain child-run detail only.
    end note

    TraceOutput --> ReturnResponse

    ReturnResponse: Shape API response
    note right of ReturnResponse
        Non-streaming returns message.content.
        Streaming returns delta.content chunks that
        reconstruct the exact final answer string.
        No trailing "Nguồn:" block is appended.
    end note

    ReturnResponse --> [*]

    ReturnApology: Return safe denial
    ReturnApology --> TraceOutput
